commit.message:
Fixed divison by zero in the computation of a direction vector in ccdMPRPenetration. (fixes #49)

In some cases, a touching contact is found in the findPenetr function. In this
case the direction vector is set to (0, 0, 0).
typo in the description of ccdMPRPenetration function
ccdVec3PointTriDist2 avoids a division by zero for ill-formed triangles (fixes #51)

commit.message:
Export declaration incorrect for windows build

Under windows, rather than defining CCD_EXPORT, _ccd_export was being
defined leading to a litany of compilation errors. This corrects the
problem.
